The paper deals with matroids, which are a fundamental concept in discrete mathematics. The focus is on reconfiguring ordered bases, which is a problem in combinatorial optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also deals with graphic matroids, which are a subclass of matroids that arise from graphs, so cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is also a likely category. The paper uses graph theory and connectivity concepts, so cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category. The paper also uses techniques from computational complexity theory, so cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is another possible category. Finally, the paper deals with optimization problems, so cs.CO (Combinatorial Optimization) is another possible category.
